DB queries; change this by either (A) fetching avatar definitions once in the
caller and passing the array into the product creation function (replace
repeated await getAvatarDefinitionsDirect() calls with a parameter like
avatarDefinitions: AvatarDefinition[]), or (B) add a small in-memory cache
inside getAvatarDefinitionsDirect (introduce module-level cachedDefinitions and
cacheTimestamp with a CACHE_TTL_MS, return cachedDefinitions when fresh,
otherwise refresh from prisma.avatarItem.findMany) so subsequent calls within
the TTL avoid DB queries; update references to getAvatarDefinitionsDirect and
any product-creation functions accordingly.
```

</details>

